## Overview

This document defines the standards for frontend development. All projects use React with TypeScript. New projects default to **Next.js (App Router)**; legacy projects may use Create React App or Vite.

> **Project-specific note**: This is a base template. Adapt the Technology Stack and Project Structure sections to match the actual project.

---

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies (adapt per project)
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router) for new projects, or React 18+ for SPAs
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode — required for all new files)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (preferred for new projects) or CSS Modules
- **UI Components**: Shadcn/ui, Radix UI, or React Bootstrap (check project before adding new ones)

### State Management & Data Flow
- **Server state**: TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) for data fetching and caching
- **Local state**: React `useState` / `useReducer` for component-level state
- **Global state**: Zustand or React Context (for simple global state only)
- **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod for validation

### Testing Framework
- **Unit & Component**: Jest + React Testing Library
- **E2E**: Cypress
- **Coverage threshold**: 80% on component logic (business logic in hooks/services)

### HTTP Client
- **Axios** or native `fetch` (Next.js) — be consistent per project
- Centralize all API calls in a service layer

