## Component Conventions

### Functional Components Only
- Always use functional components with hooks
- No class components in new code

### Component Composition (Atomic Design)
- **Atoms**: Basic UI elements (Button, Input, Badge) — usually from UI library
- **Molecules**: Combinations of atoms (SearchBar, FormField)
- **Organisms**: Complex UI sections (CandidateList, PositionCard)
- **Pages/Templates**: Full page layouts

### Props
- Destructure props in the function signature
- Provide default values for optional props
- Never pass raw objects — define a type for props

```typescript
const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({
  children,
  variant = 'primary',
  disabled = false,
  onClick,
}) => { /* ... */ };
```

### Error and Loading States
Every component that fetches data must handle all three states:

```typescript
const CandidateList: React.FC = () => {
  const { data: candidates, isLoading, error } = useCandidates();

  if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
  if (error) return <ErrorMessage message="Failed to load candidates" />;
  if (!candidates?.length) return <EmptyState message="No candidates found" />;

  return <ul>{candidates.map(c => <CandidateCard key={c.id} candidate={c} />)}</ul>;
};
```

