## API Communication

### Service Layer
Centralize all API calls in service files. Components never call APIs directly.

```typescript
// services/candidateService.ts
const API_BASE_URL = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL;

export const candidateService = {
  getAll: async (filters?: CandidateFilters): Promise<Candidate[]> => {
    const response = await axios.get(`${API_BASE_URL}/candidates`, { params: filters });
    return response.data;
  },

  create: async (data: CreateCandidateDto): Promise<Candidate> => {
    const response = await axios.post(`${API_BASE_URL}/candidates`, data);
    return response.data;
  },

  updateById: async (id: string, data: Partial<Candidate>): Promise<Candidate> => {
    const response = await axios.patch(`${API_BASE_URL}/candidates/${id}`, data);
    return response.data;
  },
};
```

### Environment Variables
- Next.js: `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for client-side variables
- CRA: `REACT_APP_*`
- Never hardcode API URLs in component or service files

