## UI/UX Standards

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML (`nav`, `main`, `article`, `button` — not `div` for interactive elements)
- Every interactive element must have an `aria-label` if purpose isn't clear from visible text
- Keyboard navigation must work for all interactive elements
- Images must have `alt` text

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) or Bootstrap grid

### Loading & Feedback
- Show loading state during async operations (Spinner or skeleton)
- Show success/error feedback after form submissions
- Disable submit buttons during loading to prevent double-submit

